import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby(['date'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='rate', data=data)
    
    plt.title('What is the trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_2010 = data[data['year'] == 2010]
    
    chart = sns.barplot(x='series', y='rate', data=data_2010)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in 2010?", wrap=True)
    
    max_rate = data_2010['rate'].max()
    max_industry = data_2010.loc[data_2010['rate'] == max_rate, 'series'].iloc[0]
    
    plt.axhline(max_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"{max_industry}: {max_rate:.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
